  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a971a2d5-184f-46e5-be81-5637c7bf6161",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Viewing the ground truth ICH segmentation masks\n",
    "\n",
    "The `mask file` column contains the file location containing the ICH mask associated with each image. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 97,
   "id": "8e65098a-d267-4eba-8f6c-9e6e0364926e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from utils import load_vol\n",
    "mask = load_vol(metadata[metadata['name'] == 'case_000']['mask file'])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f0cf7dcb-6c0a-45be-a249-9a0607760ffd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "You can filter by `name` to get the contrast and radius of the lesion (it's a sphere in this instance)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "77c223c7-a3cb-4694-8386-2100f8ae78cd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here's an example of how to get the lesion center coordinates from the mask (note the current `center x`, `center y`, `center z` values in `metadata.csv` refer to the coordinates in object space which don't necesarily equal the coordinates in the reconstructed image space due to the effects of the selected reconstructed field of view and magnification."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "89e15206-ba7b-4ee0-a74f-87f419860210",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "With these coordinates we can center the displayed image at the z slice centered about the lesion."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 98,
   "id": "ef16f83c-6315-47a2-b2a9-168fb8c5688b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x800 with 8 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from utils import get_lesion_coords\n",
    "f, axs = plt.subplots(2,2, figsize=(10,8))\n",
    "for case, ax in zip(metadata['name'].unique(), axs.flatten()):\n",
    "    z, x, y = get_lesion_coords(load_vol(metadata[metadata['name'] == case]['mask file']))\n",
    "    browse_studies(metadata, case, slice_idx=z, f=f, ax=ax)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1aac887f-0d9f-4eef-8473-bfcb19c89029",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Highlighting the lesion location with a bounding box"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 99,
   "id": "03656000",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 2400x2700 with 32 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from matplotlib.patches import Rectangle \n",
    "nrows = 5\n",
    "ncols = 5\n",
    "f, axs = plt.subplots(nrows,ncols, figsize=(nrows*4,ncols*4+2), dpi=150)\n",
    "for case, ax in zip(metadata['name'].unique(), axs.flatten()):\n",
    "    z, x, y = get_lesion_coords(load_vol(metadata[metadata['name'] == case]['mask file']))\n",
    "    browse_studies(metadata, case, slice_idx=z, f=f, ax=ax)\n",
    "    # width = 3*metadata[metadata['name'] == case]['radius'].unique()[0]\n",
    "    # ax.add_patch(Rectangle((x-width/2, y-width/2), width=width, height=width, fc ='none', ec ='g', lw = 1))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2f0b20e9-cff4-4f50-8e62-ab46ab95f733",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Highlighting the lesion location with a segmentation mask overlay"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 100,
   "id": "6b5095cb-a310-4e6f-be08-bc844411d26b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x800 with 8 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "f, axs = plt.subplots(2,2, figsize=(10,8))\n",
    "for case, ax in zip(metadata['name'].unique(), axs.flatten()):\n",
    "    mask = load_vol(metadata[metadata['name'] == case]['mask file'])\n",
    "    img = load_vol(metadata[metadata['name'] == case]['image file'])\n",
    "    z, x, y = get_lesion_coords(mask)\n",
    "    browse_studies(metadata, case, slice_idx=z, f=f, ax=ax)\n",
    "    ax.imshow(mask[z]&(img[z]>-200), cmap='Reds', alpha=0.2)"
   ]
  },
